<plot>The marriage of Ray Royle to recording company talent scout Lorraine ends in divorce after she tries to dictate both his personal and professional life. Her boss, T. J. Hopkins sends her to Memphis to sign a trio he admires. En route, she is forced to spend the night at a farmhouse where she hears Jennie Higgins sing folk songs and play the zither. Sensing that she would be a recording sensation, Lorraine takes Jennie back to New York without signing the trio. Higgins is furious and refuses to hear Jennie, so Lorraine and employees Johnny Evans and Buddy Butterfield quit and start their own small record company. Johnny tells Lorraine they need a bigger name for their initial record, so Lorraine gets her ex-husband Ray arrange to have Jennie sing at the night club where he and Gene Krupa and his Orchestra are appearing.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?216699</url></doc>
